<AdminPage ID="x33239" Name="Travel Forms" Layout="admin_office_home.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Travel Forms</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Travel Forms</Abstract><MainMesgTop type="boolean" label="Enable to move &quot;Main Message&quot; to top of page" readonly="false" required="false" hidden="false">false</MainMesgTop><IntroCopy type="dhtml" label="Main Message" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<h3><a href="https://web.byui.edu/travel/ta" title="Travel Application">Travel Application/Authorization/Reconciliation</a></h3>
<p>This portal will provide you with all the forms and information you need: As an employee - to apply for travel and reconcile completed applications. As a supervisor - to authorize Travel Applications made by employees.</p>
<h3><a href="Documents/financial-services/travel/Overnight Authorization 041514(0).pdf" title="Overnight Authorization">Overnight Student Authorization Form</a></h3>
<p>Before traveling in a group, you need to fill out this Group Travel Application form.<a href="Documents/financial-services/travel/Instructions.pdf" title="Instructions"> (instructions)</a></p>
<h3><a href="Documents/financial-services/travel/Travel Participants Roll.pdf">Travel Participation Roll</a></h3>
<p>Before having students participate in overnight travel, the sponsoring university employee must complete and turn in the forms shown above.</p>
<h3><a href="Documents/financial-services/travel/Student_Authorized_Absense_Form.pdf" title="Authorized Absence Form">Authorized Absence Policy and Request</a></h3>
<p>Students need to have each of their professors sign this form before participating in university sponsored travel that will require them to miss their academic courses.</p>
<h3><a href="Documents/financial-services/TourGroupChcklist.pdf" title="Group Travel Checklist" target="_blank">Group Travel Checklist</a></h3>
<p>Group Leaders/Directors should complete this checklist as they prepare for domestic and international student trips</p>
<h3><a href="Documents/financial-services/ActivityWaiver.pdf" title="Waiver for Student Travel and Activities" target="_blank">Waiver for Student Travel and Activities</a></h3>
<p>This waiver should be used for all non-mandatory student tours and travel or for mandatory travel if the students opt to make their own travel arrangements. An employee should complete the top portion paying special attention to the specific risks associated with that activity. Signed waivers should be retained two (2) years plus the current year unless an incident occurs then they should be retained five (5) years plus the current year.</p>
<h3><a href="http://web.byui.edu/guesttravel" title="Guest Travel Request">Guest Travel Request</a></h3>
<p>If you've got a guest traveling to the University (speaker, performer, etc.), you need to fill out this online form</p>
<h3><a href="Documents/financial-services/travel/Deviation From Itinerary Request - 03262013.pdf">Request for Deviation from Itinerary - Personal Travel</a></h3>
<p>This form should be used in situations where a travel participant requests to deviate from the travel group's planned itinerary.</p>
<h3><a href="x35093.xml#travel_reimbursements" title="Who to Call">Who to Call</a></h3>
<p>Need more information or help planning your next trip? Give us a call and we'll lend you a hand!</p>
